### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  Pacientes  ·  selecione o environment "local" no seu HTTP client
###  admin = leitura + escrita + exclusão   ·   user = apenas leitura (GET)
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Listar pacientes (USER)  → 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/pacientes
Authorization: Basic {{userAuth}}

### Cadastrar paciente (ADMIN)  → 201
# @name cadastrarPaciente
POST {{baseUrl}}/pacientes
Authorization: Basic {{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nome": "Roberto Nunes",
  "cpf": "11122233399",
  "dataNascimento": "1990-05-12",
  "telefone": "(11) 90000-0000"
}

### Buscar paciente recém-criado por ID (USER)  → 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/pacientes/{{cadastrarPaciente.response.body.$.id}}
Authorization: Basic {{userAuth}}

### Buscar paciente inexistente (USER)  → 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/pacientes/9999
Authorization: Basic {{userAuth}}

### Validação: campos vazios (ADMIN)  → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/pacientes
Authorization: Basic {{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "nome": "", "cpf": "" }

### Acesso sem autenticação  → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/pacientes

### USER tentando cadastrar (sem permissão)  → 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/pacientes
Authorization: Basic {{userAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "nome": "X", "cpf": "00000000000", "dataNascimento": "2000-01-01" }

### Remover paciente recém-criado (ADMIN)  → 204
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/pacientes/{{cadastrarPaciente.response.body.$.id}}
Authorization: Basic {{adminAuth}}
